dct_description_sm: Stanford's Geographical Estabt. ; Longmans & Co., Paternoster Row.
Relief shown by hachures, spot heights, and coloring.
"Land below sea level, coloured dark green. Land below 1000 feet, coloured light green. Land above 1000 feet, coloured brown."
Shows colonial possessions, "ancient names," waterways, anchor symbols along rivers (sometimes accompaied by "s"), international boundaries, deserts, Nile cataracts, land routes (excluding railways).
"The red figures state in inches the average rainfall of the year at the places indicated."
